# REQUIRED for unattended runs (cron/launchd): a long-lived OAuth token for
# your Claude Code / Max subscription. Generate with `claude setup-token`
# (run interactively, in your own terminal — it opens a browser login flow)
# and paste the FULL value here. Without this, `claude -p` falls back to
# your interactive session's login, which cron/launchd cannot access —
# every invocation fails with "Not logged in · Please run /login".
# Valid for about a year; see pipeline/README.md § "Token expiry" for what
# the failure looks like when it needs renewing.
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=

# Optional: model alias passed to `claude -p --model` (e.g. "sonnet", "opus"). Unset uses the CLI's default.
CLAUDE_MODEL=

# Optional: override if `claude` isn't on PATH for the process running this pipeline
CLAUDE_BIN=claude

# No API key needed at all: poll_rss.py reads the public offshoreWIND.biz RSS
# feed (no account), and the wiki-curator agent runs via `claude -p` (see
# wiki_agent.py), authenticated via CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN above rather than
# a separate pay-per-token Anthropic API key.
